  <section class="about">
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>
      At Little Diplomats, we help children and teens develop powerful English communication skills while building confidence, etiquette, and entrepreneurial thinking. Through fun and structured programs, your child will thrive both in and out of the classroom.
    </p>
    <p class="online-note">All lessons are conducted online, offering flexibility and convenience for busy families.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="programs">
    <h2>Our Programs</h2>
    <h3>Confident Communicators (Ages 6–10)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Fun English games, vocabulary, and speaking practice</li>
      <li>Basic etiquette, social skills, and dining etiquette</li>
      <li>Storytelling and show-and-tell activities</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Young Professionals (Ages 10–13)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Public speaking, teamwork, and polite communication</li>
      <li>Dining etiquette and cultural awareness</li>
      <li>Creative writing and self-expression</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Future Leaders (Ages 14–17)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Advanced communication: presentations, interviews, and essays</li>
      <li>Etiquette for life and school, including dining etiquette</li>
      <li>Critical thinking and leadership simulations</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="holiday">
    <h2>Holiday Program: In-Person Experience</h2>
    <p>
      During school holidays, we offer exclusive in-person classes that combine practical learning with fun and memorable experiences.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Interactive networking workshops to build social and communication skills</li>
      <li>Formal dining experiences that teach etiquette, confidence, and table manners</li>
      <li>Hands-on group activities that foster leadership, collaboration, and creativity</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Location:</strong> Nairobi, Kenya</p>
    <p><strong>Age Groups:</strong> 6–17 years (grouped by age)</p>
    <p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Full-day and half-day options available during school holidays</p>
  </section>

  <section class="rates">
